Cell["\<\
In classical mechanics, just like the state of motion, a physical quantity is \
described by a simple number for a scalar quantity or by a set of numbers for \
a vector quantity. As such, measurement merely assesses such number(s) and \
casts technological questions concerning only measuring devices. In quantum \
mechanics, measurement is totally different and is deeply intermingled into \
quantum theory itself.\
\>", "TechNoteText",
 CellID->474912918,ExpressionUUID->"5d0f390c-0813-4f6b-ae70-b8d05d322be5"],

