Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["No-Cloning Theorem", "Subsection",
 CellTags->"Section22",
 CellID->227743618,ExpressionUUID->"4d365c0b-8bb0-4765-ac58-fcfd5a8594dc"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "A closely related feature of quantum states is reflected in the ",
 ButtonBox["no-cloning theorem",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->"paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/tutorial/NoCloningTheorem"],
 " (Wootters and Zurek, 1982). The theorem dictates that it is impossible to \
make a copy of an ",
 StyleBox["unknown",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " quantum state. If it were possible, one could produce a bunch of identical \
copies of the same quantum state. Then, measurements of different \
incompatible observables (such as conjugate variables) on the copies would \
reveal precise information regarding the quantum state, violating the \
uncertainty principle. Cloning of an (unknown) quantum state would also allow \
faster-than- light communication. Furthermore, the no-cloning nature of \
quantum states is one of the key features of quantum mechanics that provide \
",
 StyleBox["unconditional",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " security in quantum communication."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->871128772,ExpressionUUID->"fe416724-cd26-4789-9698-5e1296784de2"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "A ",
 ButtonBox["proof of the no-cloning theorem",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->"paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/tutorial/NoCloningTheorem#1055628231"],
 " reveals that in the no-cloning nature of quantum state, crucial is the \
linearity of quantum mechanics."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->723302076,ExpressionUUID->"845f5a11-66c5-48bf-8fb4-b0732b9cb719"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Measurements on Mixed States", "Subsection",
 CellTags->"Section23",
 CellID->1804877535,ExpressionUUID->"3f8b6c2f-fef2-4f0a-a12f-8e7271b5e52f"],

Cell["\<\
In the above statement of the postulate, the system is assumed to be in a \
pure state initially, and the statement can be naturally extended to the case \
of mixed state. When a system is in a mixed state \[Rho] right before the \
measurement, the probability is given by\
\>", "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1370216870,ExpressionUUID->"13e92ec6-7146-433d-b25a-89116feb9d9b"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["P", "a"], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     TemplateBox[{"a"},
      "Bra"], "\[Rho]", 
     TemplateBox[{"a"},
      "Ket"]}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "16f65f45-db10-4d9a-8014-509963f81cc9"]
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1834354993,ExpressionUUID->"89d77c74-81cf-4123-b7a8-bd1655085316"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "and the state right after the measurement becomes ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    TemplateBox[{"a"},
     "Ket"], 
    TemplateBox[{"a"},
     "Bra"]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "c577329c-a715-47b2-9fc0-4547a9d7b6db"],
 ". By virtue of the elementary theory of probability, we observe again that ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"0", "\[LessEqual]", "\[Rho]", "\[LessEqual]", "1"}], 
   TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->"281a96b6-fabc-49c9-af27-316de53c7c7f"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"Tr", " ", "\[Rho]"}], "=", "1"}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"75dfaefe-1c2f-44c1-9ef9-0cd3175f56fa"],
 " (see ",
 ButtonBox["Mixed States",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->"paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/tutorial/QuantumStates#2028958569"],
 "). Furthermore, the expectation value of the observable is given by"
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->765761909,ExpressionUUID->"a3eab2b2-f586-4eb3-88a3-319bda109b08"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"\[LeftAngleBracket]", "A", "\[RightAngleBracket]"}], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      SubscriptBox["\[Sum]", "a"], 
      RowBox[{"a", " ", 
       SubscriptBox["P", "a"]}]}], "=", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{
       SubscriptBox["\[Sum]", "a"], 
       RowBox[{"a", 
        TemplateBox[{"a"},
         "Bra"], "\[Rho]", 
        TemplateBox[{"a"},
         "Ket"]}]}], "=", 
      RowBox[{"Tr", " ", "A", " ", "\[Rho]"}]}]}]}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"1511783b-7691-4f25-aae7-b0a4ed795b85"],
 " ."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1767787309,ExpressionUUID->"da848011-5e8c-4e33-a493-ca2d6cc8e1cc"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Von Neumann Scheme of Projective Measurements", "Subsection",
 CellTags->"Section24",
 CellID->765046118,ExpressionUUID->"0f9bbc98-9969-45ac-9789-e6115a3bc280"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Von Neumann envisioned an idealistic procedure to perform a projective \
measurement on physical systems. For this reason, projective measurement is \
also referred to as a von Neumann measurement. The von Neumann scheme laid \
the foundation for the quantum theory of measurement, and it has inspired \
various methods to improve the measurement precision towards the intrinsic \
limit of quantum mechanics. The von Neumann scheme for projective measurement \
can be implemented directly in a ",
 ButtonBox["quantum circuit model",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->"paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/ref/QuantumCircuit"],
 ". Here, we briefly summarize the procedure."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->212867608,ExpressionUUID->"8c419dd3-4a71-4cac-a29b-a23465156613"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Suppose that we want to measure a quantity described by a Hermitian \
operator ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["A", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "7d721f01-e4e4-4dac-85e2-c39786c5f50b"],
 ". Let ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[{"a"},
    "Ket"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "5f47992d-7fb2-4181-b624-aa343e44d69c"],
 " be the eigenvectors with eigenvalues ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["a", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "78eecd7a-15c4-4dff-86f0-f4e8b2c44a9e"],
 " of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["A", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "539e957b-e50e-493a-800f-1140c9a3bd8d"],
 " so that ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["A", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "464b9572-fa9b-43ab-a429-0b1317ee5694"],
 " has spectral decomposition"
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->2105615401,ExpressionUUID->"f5877a53-5138-4377-9313-ed3d7dd937b5"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"A", "=", 
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox["\[Sum]", "a"], 
     RowBox[{
      TemplateBox[{"a"},
       "Ket"], "a", 
      TemplateBox[{"a"},
       "Bra"]}]}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "1ba9fbf0-b5cf-48c3-b359-0b1e588b3b57"],
 "."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->695025694,ExpressionUUID->"b12e1b22-9765-4242-83eb-2395f4d1c7a9"],

Cell["The system is in a state |\[Psi]\:27e9, which is expanded as", \
"TechNoteText",
 CellID->1133283025,ExpressionUUID->"89c9f682-ab91-4881-80f1-e71f849aeb18"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    TemplateBox[{"\[Psi]"},
     "Ket"], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox["\[Sum]", "a"], 
     RowBox[{
      TemplateBox[{"a"},
       "Ket"], 
      SubscriptBox["\[Psi]", "a"]}]}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "ac8a3c68-7916-4c11-9903-101af2858fea"]
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1055335932,ExpressionUUID->"9058e444-ac8d-489b-94c2-d5be6bd1421b"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "in the eigenbasis of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["A", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "af15b69c-1b49-4e3e-83f7-ec4bb1fcc31e"],
 ". Typically, the probability distribution ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["P", "a"], ":=", 
    SuperscriptBox[
     RowBox[{"\[LeftBracketingBar]", 
      SubscriptBox["\[Psi]", "a"], "\[RightBracketingBar]"}], "2"]}], 
   TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->"ad991218-554e-4b8e-b0c7-66adc05b3c55"],
 " is supposed to sharply peak around a certain unknown eigenstate ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[{
     SubscriptBox["a", "*"]},
    "Ket"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "3d331642-433b-4a7d-8a2b-8dfb397cbf70"],
 ", and the measurement is supposed to reveal ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["a", "*"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "86ea1231-0c06-445c-bc13-a5da2fc78376"],
 "."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->963568551,ExpressionUUID->"20990341-6df3-4208-8259-ca709f1e6e07"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "We choose a measuring device with \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]position\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["X", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "0af31d27-94f3-4749-9c54-3dd25bbc836d"],
 ", which can be directly observed, and we prepare it in an approximate \
eigenstate |\[Xi]\:27e9 of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["X", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "2f6720ac-17ed-4071-89e3-e587acfc819e"],
 ". In terms of eigenstates ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[{"x"},
    "Ket"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "bd6f817e-5308-49f0-b200-612064e17a05"],
 " with eigenvalue ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["x", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "558983b4-6712-49b4-a816-38695ac44f0f"],
 " of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["X", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "3108438e-8d7e-4ba6-9eb3-fc8572a58738"],
 ", |\[Xi]\:27e9 is expanded as"
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->522454630,ExpressionUUID->"0b31e371-f5bb-406a-b36b-905ac21fcc1d"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    TemplateBox[{"\[Xi]"},
     "Ket"], "=", 
    RowBox[{"\[Integral]", 
     RowBox[{"d", " ", "x", 
      TemplateBox[{"x"},
       "Ket"], 
      RowBox[{"\[Xi]", "(", "x", ")"}]}]}]}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"84670219-ce81-40c8-b72e-99a53c0c4663"]
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1981817474,ExpressionUUID->"f13dd98c-bed1-48da-9122-076154024f40"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "with ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"\[Xi]", 
    RowBox[{"(", "x", ")"}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "c2bf69ff-1757-487b-959e-26c7979563e2"],
 " having a sharp peak around a certain fixed point x0. It will become clear \
below how a sharper distribution ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox[
    RowBox[{"\[LeftBracketingBar]", 
     RowBox[{"\[Xi]", "(", "x", ")"}], "\[RightBracketingBar]"}], "2"], 
   TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->"2f3c9180-f378-4547-903c-b7e40c83c26e"],
 " in the position results in a more accurate measurement. At this stage, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    TemplateBox[{"\[Psi]"},
     "Ket"], "\[CircleTimes]", 
    TemplateBox[{"\[Xi]"},
     "Ket"]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "5e0d5fb5-f33f-4788-9706-2b960f098c26"],
 " is the overall state of the total system containing the system to be \
measured and the measurement device."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->934920548,ExpressionUUID->"598d516f-62b9-4928-aa07-6b21be50db77"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Now couple the observable ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["A", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "a462624b-d4e9-4904-856e-864ed5a9a163"],
 " in question to the \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]momentum\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] \
",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["P", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "60778fd0-37a6-4619-9d69-83dcbc5d6ae4"],
 " (not ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["X", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "e138cfb4-4ec4-4347-bd9c-055713b2df20"],
 " itself) of the measurement device. Note that ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["P", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "24927fbf-b376-400b-9b0d-a4c58bb45d03"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["X", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "fc0b4e26-5e63-45a6-8227-98f6123e9c35"],
 " are canonical conjugates of each other such that ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"[", 
     RowBox[{"X", ",", "P"}], "]"}], "=", "\[ImaginaryI]"}], 
   TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->"55f59288-d122-482c-8540-250012cd4bdc"],
 " (recall that we have chosen a unit system such that  ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"\[HBar]", "=", "1"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "6602b3cf-c47c-4f04-b227-369294655d39"],
 "). The coupling is described by the interaction Hamiltonian"
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->71805137,ExpressionUUID->"2e608ee9-efb6-4d7f-a977-ea8d9665ab45"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["H", "int"], "=", 
    RowBox[{"J", " ", 
     RowBox[{"P", "\[CircleTimes]", "A"}]}]}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"22129938-cbd6-4933-b903-0b63b259cce6"],
 " ,"
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->2090611592,ExpressionUUID->"55ab0092-7165-41af-b0a9-a3577e48556c"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "where ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["J", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "5e49039a-8566-46b4-b50d-3df22ce8ee50"],
 " is the coupling strength. One has to let the system and the measurement \
device interact for a sufficiently long time \[Tau] such that the position of \
the measurement device is distinguished from the initial position. Let ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"g", ":=", 
    RowBox[{"J", " ", "\[Tau]"}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "251c0941-b8a8-4622-b087-6ebf49406a70"],
 " be the dimensionless coupling constant. Due to coupling, the total system \
composed of the system in question and the measurement device evolves over \
time, which is described by the unitary operator"
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1929078177,ExpressionUUID->"ae09345b-a0eb-4438-8a2d-f42e1483d063"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["U", "int"], "=", 
    RowBox[{"exp", "(", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"-", "\[ImaginaryI]"}], " ", "g", " ", 
      RowBox[{"P", "\[CircleTimes]", "A"}]}], ")"}]}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"5412f8b3-e6e2-4d05-93f4-022d6d9fc740"],
 " ."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1456302080,ExpressionUUID->"7b1316bf-e2cf-413f-b87a-55a54bd2d9a9"],

